{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#4010: Should keyed v-for array refs be ordered?",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:27:30.856681+00:00",
  "text": "Should keyed v-for array refs be ordered?\n\n### Version\r\n3.1.2\r\n\r\n### Reproduction link\r\n[vue 3](https://codesandbox.io/s/falling-darkness-dlhz2?file=/src/components/HelloWorld.vue)\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n1. open sandbox\r\n2. open console\r\n3. click reverse\r\n4. see first and second refs log\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\nsecond log should be:\r\n```\r\n[\r\n  <div>bar</div>,\r\n  <div>foo</div>,\r\n]\r\n```\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\nsecond log still be:\r\n```\r\n[\r\n  <div>foo</div>,\r\n  <div>bar</div>,\r\n]\r\n```\r\n\r\n<!-- generated by vue-issues. DO NOT REMOVE -->\r\n\r\nRef: https://v3.vuejs.org/guide/migration/array-refs.html",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "need guidance",
    "scope: v2 compat"
  ],
